\begin_layout Standard
A large literature in behavioral economics suggests that biases such as
 self-control problems, inattention, and incorrect beliefs can lead to over-cons
umption of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

sin goods
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 such as cigarettes, alcohol, unhealthy foods, and energy-inefficient durable
 goods.
 Consumption of these goods can also generate externalities in the form
 of health care costs or pollution.
 Consequently, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

sin taxes
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 that discourage consumption of such goods could increase social welfare.
 This argument has led to widespread taxation of cigarettes and alcohol,
 as well as newer taxes on sugar-sweetened beverages in seven U.S.
 cities and 34 countries around the world (GFRP 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citeyear
key "GFRP2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What is the optimal level of a sin tax? The existing literature frequently
 invokes a corrective logic dating to 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Pigou1920"
literal "true"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Diamond1973"
literal "true"

\end_inset

: the optimal corrective tax equals the sum of the externality and the average
 mistake (or 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

internality
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

) of marginal consumers.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fn:average marginal bias"

\end_inset

For Pigouvian taxation of internalities, see 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "ODonoghue2006"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Gruber2001"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet*
key "Allcott2014"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Allcott2015"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Heutel"
literal "true"

\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet*
key "Mullainathan2012"
literal "true"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset

