 utility of money, and thus that policymakers care equally about the poor
 versus the rich.
 This assumption is starkly out of sync with public debates about sin taxes.
 As highlighted by the above quote from Senator Bernie Sanders, a common
 objection to sin taxes is that they are regressive.
