\begin_layout Standard
The second term in our optimal commodity tax formula represents the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

corrective motive
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

: the desire to reduce over-consumption arising from internalities and externali
ties by imposing taxes on harmful goods.
 To incorporate internalities, we follow the sufficient statistics approach
 to behavioral public finance (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp*
key "Farhi2015,chetty2015,Mullainathan2012"
literal "true"

\end_inset

