\begin_layout Standard
To characterize the optimal commodity tax, it is helpful to define the 
\emph on
social marginal utility of income, 
\emph default
denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{g}(z)$
\end_inset

, which is defined (as in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Farhi2015"
literal "true"

\end_inset

) as the average welfare effect of marginally increasing the disposable
 incomes of consumers currently earning income 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset

.
 The weights 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{g}(z)$
\end_inset

 incorporate any fiscal externalities resulting from income effects, and
 also the social welfare effect from mis-spending this marginal income due
 to bias.
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fn:g-hat"

\end_inset

Formally, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{g}(z^{*})=g(z^{*})+\mathbb{E}\left[\eta_{z}(\theta)\frac{T'}{1-T'}|z(\theta)=z^{*}\right]+\mathbb{E}\left[(t-g(\theta)\gamma(\theta)-e)\left(\frac{\eta(\theta)}{p+t}+\frac{\eta_{z}(\theta)}{1-T'}\frac{\xi(\theta)s(\theta)}{z(\theta)}\right)\mid z(\theta)=z^{*}\right]$
\end_inset

.
 See Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app: general prop proof"

\end_inset

 for further details.
 If Assumption 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "assump:additional"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 holds, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{g}=g$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 In Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:opt tax in mswws"

\end_inset

, we provide formulas expressed entirely in terms of the social marginal
 welfare weights 
\begin_inset Formula $g(z)$
\end_inset

.
 All proofs are contained in Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app: general prop proof"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proposition
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop:general opt tax"

\end_inset

