 Moreover, the internality correction is further inflated by about 
\begin_inset CommandInset include
LatexCommand input
filename "../../Output/Simulations/NumbersForText/sigma100.tex"

\end_inset

percent due to the bias correction progressivity term 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

, reflecting the fact that the benefits of bias correction accrue disproportiona
tely to poorer consumers.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Counteracting this corrective motive, the redistributive motive pushes toward
 a smaller optimal SSB tax, because the poor have much stronger preferences
 for SSBs than the wealthy.
 Using Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:ManualTable"

\end_inset

, we can calculate 
\begin_inset Formula $Cov[g(z),s(z)]\approx\input{../../Output/Simulations/NumbersForText/covgs.tex}$
\end_inset

