 based on actual SSB consumption, while the second represents the change
 in income tax revenues due to the effect of the SSB tax on labor supply.
 Thus the redistributive motive reduces the tax by about 20 percent relative
 to the pure corrective motive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The baseline calculation above holds fixed the status quo income tax.
 If the optimal income tax is allowed to adjust to be optimal, the impact
