\begin_layout Standard
We now characterize the optimal commodity tax when the income tax is suboptimal
 at some fixed 
\begin_inset Formula $T(z)$
\end_inset

, assuming 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{z}$
\end_inset

 are negligible, and that 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta_{z}$
\end_inset

 , 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

 are uncorrelated conditional on income.
 We can begin with the derivation for 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{dW}{dt}$
\end_inset

 on lines 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dWdT_1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

