A composite sin good can be represented in the utility function by assuming
 that consumers maximize decision utility 
\begin_inset Formula $U(c,s_{1},s_{2},\ldots,s_{n},z;\theta)$
\end_inset

 subject to their budget constraint 
\begin_inset Formula $c+(1+\tau)\sum_{i=1}^{n}p_{i}s_{i}\leq z-T(z)$
