As in the proof of Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop:general opt tax"

\end_inset

 above, consider the implications of a small joint perturbation to the commodity
 tax 
\begin_inset Formula $d\tau$
\end_inset

, combined with an offsetting compensation through the income tax which
