 are locally constant and are underweighted by some constant amount due
 to present bias or incorrect beliefs.
 In general, a sufficient condition is that 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma_{i}$
\end_inset

 is locally constant in 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

.
 Substituting the 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 subscript for the 
\begin_inset Formula $(p,y,\theta)$
\end_inset

 triple and re-arranging gives 
\begin_inset Formula $\ln s_{i}=\ln s_{i}^{V}+\zeta_{i}^{c}\gamma_{i}/p_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Compensated elasticity is 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta_{i}^{c}=\zeta_{i}-\frac{\xi_{i}}{1-T'(z_{i})}\cdot\frac{p_{i}s_{i}}{z_{i}}$
\end_inset

, because 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta^{c}=\zeta-\frac{ds}{dy}p$
\end_inset

 per the Slutsky equation, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{ds}{dy}p=\frac{ds}{dz}\frac{dz}{dy}p=\frac{ds}{dz}\frac{1}{1-T'(z)}p=\frac{\xi}{1-T'(z)}\frac{ps}{z}$
\end_inset

.
 We use the 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta_{i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi_{i}$
\end_inset

 estimated at household 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

's income from Appendix Table 
