 purpose of understanding the robustness of our estimates.
 However, one might also wish to understand how more extreme variations
 in parameters affect the optimal sin tax.
 In particular, the analytic formulas in Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Model"

\end_inset

 emphasize the role of bias and elasticity of demand in determining the
 optimal tax.
 In order to illustrate those insights quantitatively, Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
